        "generateUrl": "https://modal.com/settings/tokens",
        "setup": "Go to the [Modal tokens settings](https://modal.com/settings/tokens) and create a new token. Modal documents the credential pair as a token ID and token secret, with `ak-` / `as-` prefixes. You can also mint or set them locally with `modal token new` or `modal token set`. Store the pair in `.modal.toml` or set `MODAL_TOKEN_ID` and `MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET`."
      },
      "modal_proxy_token": {
        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Modal Proxy Token",
        "generateUrl": "https://modal.com/settings/workspaces",
        "setup": "Open your [Workspace settings](https://modal.com/settings/workspaces), then manage [Proxy Tokens](https://modal.com/docs/guide/webhook-proxy-auth). Create a proxy token for your Workspace. Modal says the token ID and secret use `wk-` and `ws-` prefixes, and they authenticate to HTTP interfaces on Modal Servers and Web Functions via the `Modal-Key` and `Modal-Secret` headers. These are distinct from API tokens."
      }
